         b'2>Are you downloading copyrighted files? You are out!</h2>\n\n'
         b'\t\t\t<div class="entry">\n\t\t\t\t<p>A proposal(*) backed by French'
         b' president Nicolas Sarkozy: those people who download copyrighted ma'
         b'terial (using, for example, P2P networks) will get disconnected from'
         b' the Internet by their ISPs.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Like it or not, the t'
         b'otal cost of Internet service will rise because French ISPs have sig'
         b'ned on to the plan. They will now spend time and (tax) money enforci'
         b'ng copyright on their networks via expensive deep packet inspection '
         b'(DPI) software that will monitor traffic on their networks and look '
         b'for copyrighted content. Subscribers detected illicitly sharing or d'
         b'ownloading copyrighted material will receive warnings, requiring add'
         b'itional administrative overhead. If the behavior continues, then Int'
         b'ernet access would be guillotined. Most of this will be carried out '
         b'by a government-funded independent authority overseen by a judge&#82'
         b'21; (<a href="http://arstechnica.com/news.ars/post/20071125-the-insa'
         b'nity-and-genius-of-frances-anti-file-sharing-plan.html">full post</a'
         b'>).</p>\n<p>(*)<font size="-1"> I do not describe the proposal as'
         b' being insane just for this reason: &#8220;Do not be hectoring or ar'
         b'rogant. Those who disagree with you are not necessarily <strong>stup'
         b'id</strong> or <strong>insane</strong>. Nobody needs to be described'
         b' as silly: let your analysis show that he is. When you express opini'
         b'ons, do not simply make    assertions. The aim is not just to tell r'
         b'eaders what you think, but to persuade them; if you use arguments, r'
         b'easoning and    evidence, you may succeed. Go easy on the oughts and'
         b' shoulds. &#8221; You may well understand to which category Mr. Sark'
         b'ozy qualifies to belong.<br />\n</font></p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t'
