         b'files-you-are-out/#comment-1346">\n\t\t\tNovember 27, 2007 at 5:56 p'
         b'm</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<p>Do the warnings happen on a per file or '
         b'per session basis? There is probably no point in even having warning'
         b's if its 3-files-and-you&#8217;re-out.</p>\n<p>Interestingly enou'
         b'gh though, this is the first legislative response to the ongoing deb'
         b'ate about DRM. The big tech companies have had plenty to say (let&#8'
         b'217;s lock people into our legal technologies), as have all the majo'
         b'r record labels (let&#8217;s sue people who download). Any ideas for'
         b' alternatives? Should the government stay out of this completely?</p'
         b'>\n\n\t\t<div class="reply">\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n'
         b'\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t\t<li class="comment byuser comm'
