         b'ou-downloading-copyrighted-files-you-are-out/#comment-1352">\n\t\t\t'
         b'November 28, 2007 at 9:08 am</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<p>From what I u'
         b'nderstood about Chiariglione&#8217;s proposal (which seems quite blu'
         b'rry to me), the difference with present-day DRM is just that the enc'
         b'ryption algorithms are standard. The encryption key is obviously sti'
         b'll secret. For interoperability, there should be an entity that deci'
         b'des if your system is secure enough to obtain access to a certified '
         b'key&#8230; And, if I&#8217;m not wrong, a single compromised certifi'
         b'ed item would be enough to tear all the DRM architecture apart.<'
         b'/p>\n\n\t\t<div class="reply">\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div'
